@<section "Settlers">
@<illustration image="../f/esiedler.png">
@Settlers are needed to found new towns. And for the sake of prosperity lots of towns
@are of utmost importance. Prudently start expanding your Empire by founding
@your second town by turn two. Because there is a dictated minimum distance of 3 ½ squares
@(Diagonals count as 1 ½ square) between your towns, your settlers should move out a  
@bit beforehand. All your towns should be raised on fertile grounds. 
@Perfectly suited are Grasslands (or Cultivated Lands), an Oasis also does the trick.
@Referring to our example,  <b>-3,1</b> looks like a good location.
@Your new town will be founded by using the <b><a href="SG.htm">FC</a></b> command, don´t
@forget to add the town´s name. Your very first settler unit bears the same abbreviation as your
@Empire, except a 1 is appended. </illustration>
@<itemize>
@<example><b>
@EMA1 &nbsp; MVNW,W,W &nbsp; FCCLAUSTROPHOPOLIS
@</b></example>
@</itemize>
